==English==

===Adjective===
'''childlike'''

# Of, like, or suitable for a [[child]]; [[meek]]; [[submissive]].
# [[innocent|Innocent]] and [[trustful]]; [[credulous]]; [[artless]].
# Of, or like a [[baby]]; [[infantile]].

====Quotations====
*'''1859''': [[w:Henry Barnard|Henry Barnard]], ''Pestalozzi and Pestalozzianism''
*: And on the other hand, fatherly and '''childlike''' feelings in the national spirit, are the sources of all pure national blessings.
*'''1894''': [[w:Gotthold Ephraim Lessing|Gotthold Ephraim Lessing]], 	''Lessings Nathan Der Weise''
*: He certainly has '''childlike''' simplicity, and all the qualities which go to make up a true Christian character.

